Krnica [kurnitsa] (German Krnitz) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Krapkowice, within Krapkowice County, Opole Voivodeship, in south-western Poland.[1] It lies approximately 9 kilometres (6mi) south-west of Krapkowice and 30km (19mi) south of the regional capital Opole. Before 1945 the area was part of Germany (see Territorial changes of Poland after World War II).  Coordinates: 5024N 1755E / 50.4N 17.917E / 50.4; 17.917
